<br>
Its likely my accounts in EQ will be banned in the next 3 days anyway.  The mods at the mage tower spoke to their contacts within SoE, they cited my negitive tude in regards to the game and provided numerous posts.  I was in turn contacted in regard to this to inform me that I could be facing possible banning even though my account has not recieved even 1 warning.  This was not an offical SoE e-mail or communication but just discussion with one of their representives.<br>
<br>
Oh, and if you believe that soE will not ban somone for simply negitive opinions on messgae boards you are incorrect.  It ha s been done before, it is their game and they can do anything they wish to.<br>
<br>
My issues at the mage tower were caused by the fact I believed the magician class required additonal upgrades that were not present in SoV, SoL, or PoP expansions.  When challanged and flamed I flamed back.  In retrospect I should have simply stopped posting on the mage tower.  During the last 12 months my message has been simple and mostly free of flames there, I tried hard to point out where the class is lacking.<br>
<br>
What set the mods off and the entire mage community this time is when I challanged the objectivity of the mods in regards to a MMOG they reviewed.  Infact the very post that got me banned was:  &quot;So it looks like &lt;insert name of company&gt; is buying a fanbase&quot;.  <br>
<br>
That post was made because I had an issue with the mods accepting expense paid trips and first class accomodations to review a MMOG.  No, this was not SoE.. it was another company. <br>
<br>
I found out several months ago that the mods are not interested in any sort of discussion there that might upset SoE.  In other words they want only happy mages that like the state of the class and do not wish to see improvments to post there.<br>
<br>
Just proves my points 2 times over.  Too many children playing too many political games.  Hell I'm not getting paid to play this game and I have about had it.  So they win.. &lt;golf clap&gt;.  Mage class stays the same.. no improvment and I get to spend time doing somehting else.  Whatever.<br>
